Along the making of our code, some features from the original plan were changed 
to improve the program. In the original version, the program only asked the user 
to manually enter percentages for categories like savings, food, necessities, 
wants, and school purposes. In the updated version, 10% of the allowance is 
automatically deducted for emergency funds to make sure that users always have
money saved for unexpected situations.

The categories were also updated to Toiletries, Miscellaneous, Food, and School, 
which are more common expenses for students. Another improvement is that the program
now shows how many percent are left to allocate after each input, helping users keep 
track of their budget more easily.

Some planned features, such as asking if the budget is weekly or monthly and adding
more categories after the main input, were removed to keep the program simpler and more
focused on the main budgeting function.
